Original single from the  Lambsbread “Love in the house” on the @zionhighproductions riddim “Liberation” performed live on Maui. This was our first single and was originally released on 45 in Jamaica in 2003 alongside tunes from @capletonmusic Yami Bolo @lutanfyahmusic @turbulence_big_lion This was the first time a reggae artist from Hawaii was released on vinyl in Jamaica. Big up @jahdavid777 for helping to introduce Lambsbread to the world 🌍 #lambsbread #reggaemusic #liberationriddim #hawaiireggae #rootsreggae #loveinthehouse #riddim #maui #kauai #capleton #turbulence #lutanfyah #reggaefestival #cooyah

social_posts.post_text: Maui people 📣 Get ready for #reggaeinthegarden Saturday May 27th  at the beautiful @southmauigardens in Kihei, this is an outdoor all ages event sponsored by @q103maui featuring @thelambsbread special guest @messenjah_selah will be in the house, opening up will be @kalolu_the_band and @eb.flow plus soundsystem vibes from @elihusound 🔊🔊🔊dropping the freshest reggae jams, South Maui gardens is a hidden Oasis 🌴 in Kihei a block up from Kalama park, there will be a variety of food trucks, craft vendors, a kava bar and more! Gates open at 4:20 🔥💨💨💨 early bird tickets 🎟️ only $25 and are on sale now at eventbrite.com ticket link in bio  #maui #reggae #mauievents #reggaefestival #reggaeconcert #livemusicmaui #lambsbread #messenjahselah #southmauigardens #mauievents

Celebrating my family Chris Meredith, today on his earthstrong, it’s been one year since his passing, but I still miss him every day. He was an exemplary human being and one of the greatest bass players of all time. A true legend that played on so much reggae hits, too many to count. It was an honor to know him and play music with him. This was the last song he produced for us, and it always brings a joy (and a little sadness) to my heart when I hear it now. Wish I could call you, guess I have to do it through the spirt now, Chris always believed in us and our music, and from the first time we worked together he played on everything we recorded till his passing, I can still hear him say “which is right” miss you my brother #lambsbread #chrismeredith #legend #bass #realone #family #stephenmarley

We recorded this song a few years ago, but the message is still just as relevant right now. Oppression, war and suffering are rampant on the earth, these criminal warlords that are in power are devoid of compassion, it is the people that suffer, the innocent, the children, the mothers and fathers. It doesn’t matter what color, race, religion, side you are from, we all want the same thing, to be safe, for our families to have food cloths and shelter, violence is used as a tool for control. The amount of resources that are wasted for weapons is staggering, just to keep a group of evil soulless beings in power, when we could live in peace with some healing and education. Here is an interesting 🤔 fact that can easily be verified with a google search, worldwide we humans spend 2.24 Trillion dollars on Weapons annually, and that amount has grown steadily for the past few years. This insane amount of money 💰 is supposed to protect us from each other. But where is all this money coming from? Your paycheck….is it worth it? Weapons manufacturers want you to think so, as they extract more and more yearly through the politicians they put in place, presidents and prime minister, some that can barely formulate a sentence, they don’t care about any of us. The end goal is global domination. Will we wake up? Will we put a stop to it, as everyone struggles to pay their bills will they have time to think about any of this?

Superiority is an illusion, if your religion, race, nationality or place you are from makes you feel superior to others, you are under an illusion, feeling superior to others also allows people to feel justified when subjugating and committing violence against those they view as less. 
Religions do a lot to divide people, by making their followers feel superior to others, governments also feed the division. If we could see that we are not that much different, even if we come from different cultures or ideologies, we could live in harmony and see the beauty of our variety. Every one with something to add to benefit, instead of destroying and eliminating a different way of life. We have been living in this war culture globally for a long time. We have advanced our civilization, technology, convenience and communication greatly, but when it comes to our evolution of consciousness we still practice the same cave man policy, only now with bigger more powerful technologically advanced weaponry. All under the guise that we are protecting ourselves from each other. It is time we make a great step forward and eliminate war as an option to solving anything. It never has. They say insanity is doing the same thing over and over and expecting different results, that is what we need to realize about war, war is insanity. One day when war doesn’t exist on this planet 🌍 it will be because no one is left that is willing to fight it.  Also last but not least, self defense is not the same as revenge. #onelove #oneheart #onepeople #love #togetherness #peace #nomorewar #stopthekilling #weareone

• May the veil of illusion be lifted from the eyes of humanity •

Each day we witness more and more un-fathomable atrocities being committed on our planet. It is becoming harder and harder for our hearts to bear the cries of the innocent children, the mothers, the fathers, the grandmothers & grandfathers. Harder for ones to turn their heads & carry on with the regular day to day reality. Harder for the people in the war zones to breathe, to live, to mourn, to just simply wake up to a new day.

It’s not getting better for them, the bombs keep dropping, the snippers are still shooting, the people are still dying. This oppression is nothing new, for hundreds of years we have witnessed the destruction of colonialism. When we wrote this song so many years ago, I could never imagine that I would see & hear what my eyes are seeing right now. Because of social media and those who are not afraid to share the reality of the world, the truth is available for all to see. Today these lyrics are hitting my heart in a way they hadn’t before, the tears flow from my eyes watering the seeds of tomorrow’s fruits. 

InI will always stand for dismantling the corrupt systems that rule & oppress the people of the world. We will always stand for truth, for love, for unity, for peace, for freedom, for a better way.

#worldneedslove #humanity #setthemfree #peaceandlove #betterways #newearth #freedomfighters
